TmnxPppCpState.name: TmnxPppCpState
TmnxPppCpState.description: The TmnxPppCpState data type is an enumerated integer that describes the current status of a PPP link. It can be applied to both LCP and NCP links.

tmnxPppTable.name: tmnxPppTable
tmnxPppTable.description: The tmnxPppTable has an entry for each port in the system that is configured for PPP.

tmnxPppEntry.name: tmnxPppEntry
tmnxPppEntry.description: Each row entry represents a port from the tmnxPortTable that is configured for PPP. Entries cannot be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations.

tmnxPppLinkPhase.name: tmnxPppLinkPhase
tmnxPppLinkPhase.description: The current link phase for this PPP connection.

tmnxPppLocalAddress.name: tmnxPppLocalAddress
tmnxPppLocalAddress.description: The Ip address assigned the local end of the PPP link. This object was made obsolete in the 4.0 release.

tmnxPppRemoteAddress.name: tmnxPppRemoteAddress
tmnxPppRemoteAddress.description: The Ip address of the remote end of the PPP link. This object was made obsolete in the 4.0 release.

tmnxPppRemoteMacAddress.name: tmnxPppRemoteMacAddress
tmnxPppRemoteMacAddress.description: The Ethernet MacAddress sent by the remote end of the PPP link.

tmnxPppLineMonitorMethod.name: tmnxPppLineMonitorMethod
tmnxPppLineMonitorMethod.description: The type of line monitoring packets being sent and received on this PPP link. Note that this can be deduced from the values of tmnxPppKaPeriod and tmnxPppQuality. One can find out whether lqm or keepalive is enabled or not. That is, lqm is enabled (keepalive is disabled) if tmnxPppQuality is not zero; and keepalive is enabled if tmnxPppKaPeriod is not zero and tmnxPppQuality is zero. If tmnxPppQuality and tmnxPppKaPeriod are both set to zero, no line monitoring is used.

tmnxPppKaPeriod.name: tmnxPppKaPeriod
tmnxPppKaPeriod.description: The value tmnxPppKaPeriod is used to configure the time interval in seconds at which keepalive requests are issued. When LQM is enabled by setting tmnxPppQuality equal to some value other than zero (0), keepalives are replaced with LQR messages.

tmnxPppKaDropCount.name: tmnxPppKaDropCount
tmnxPppKaDropCount.description: The value of tmnxPppKaDropCount determines how many keepalive or LQR messages can be missed before the line is brought down.

tmnxPppKaLastClearedTime.name: tmnxPppKaLastClearedTime
tmnxPppKaLastClearedTime.description: The last time that keepalive stats were cleared. Note that the keepalive stats are cleared when changing from LQM to keepalives or vice versa.

tmnxPppKaThresholdExceedsCount.name: tmnxPppKaThresholdExceedsCount
tmnxPppKaThresholdExceedsCount.description: The number of times that tmnxPppKaDropCount was reached.

tmnxPppKaInPktCount.name: tmnxPppKaInPktCount
tmnxPppKaInPktCount.description: The number of echo-reply packets received.

tmnxPppKaOutPktCount.name: tmnxPppKaOutPktCount
tmnxPppKaOutPktCount.description: The number of echo-request packets sent.

tmnxPppKaTimeDropLink.name: tmnxPppKaTimeDropLink
tmnxPppKaTimeDropLink.description: The time remaining before the link will be declared dropped if a keepalive echo reply packet is not received.

tmnxPppQuality.name: tmnxPppQuality
tmnxPppQuality.description: The value of tmnxPppQuality is a percentage used by LQM to monitor the link quality. If the quality drops below this percentage, the router shuts down the link. The percentages are calculated for both the incoming and outgoing directions. When LQM is enabled by setting tmnxPppQuality to a non-zero value, Link Quality Reports (LQRs) are sent, in place of keepalives, every keepalive period. All incoming keepalives and/or LQRs are always responded to regardless of the setting of tmnxPppQuality. A value of zero (0) implies no LQM quality monitoring and is the only value supported.

tmnxPppLqmOperPeriod.name: tmnxPppLqmOperPeriod
tmnxPppLqmOperPeriod.description: The value tmnxPppLqmOperPeriod is the negotiated time interval in seconds at which LQM LQR requests are issued.

tmnxPppLqmInRate.name: tmnxPppLqmInRate
tmnxPppLqmInRate.description: The average of 'SaveInPackets'/'PeerOutPackets' in the last five consecutive LQRs received.

tmnxPppLqmOutRate.name: tmnxPppLqmOutRate
tmnxPppLqmOutRate.description: The average of 'PeerInPackets'/'LastOutPackets' in the last five consecutive LQRs received.

tmnxPppLqmLastClearedTime.name: tmnxPppLqmLastClearedTime
tmnxPppLqmLastClearedTime.description: The last time that LQM stats were cleared.

tmnxPppLqmThresholdExceedsCount.name: tmnxPppLqmThresholdExceedsCount
tmnxPppLqmThresholdExceedsCount.description: The number of times that either tmnxPppLqmInRate or tmnxPppLqmOutRate falls below the specified quality percentage when PPP quality or LQM is enforced.

tmnxPppLqmInPktCount.name: tmnxPppLqmInPktCount
tmnxPppLqmInPktCount.description: The number of LQR packets received.

tmnxPppLqmOutPktCount.name: tmnxPppLqmOutPktCount
tmnxPppLqmOutPktCount.description: The number of LQR packets sent.

tmnxPppLqmTimeDropLink.name: tmnxPppLqmTimeDropLink
tmnxPppLqmTimeDropLink.description: The time remaining before the link will be declared dropped if a LQM LQR message packet is not received.

tmnxPppLocalMagicNumber.name: tmnxPppLocalMagicNumber
tmnxPppLocalMagicNumber.description: tmnxPppLocalMagicNumber is the local magic number to be sent to the peer. The magic number provides a method to detect loopbacks. If the value of tmnxPppLocalMagicNumber is the same as the value of tmnxPppRemoteMagicNumber, then it is possible that the link might be looped back. If the two magic numbers do not match, then the link is not looped back.

tmnxPppRemoteMagicNumber.name: tmnxPppRemoteMagicNumber
tmnxPppRemoteMagicNumber.description: tmnxPppRemoteMagicNumber is the magic number sent by the peer. If the value of tmnxPppRemoteMagicNumber is the same as the value of tmnxPppLocalMagicNumber, then it is possible that the link might be looped back. If the two magic numbers do not match, then the link is not looped back.

tmnxPppLocalIPv4AddressType.name: tmnxPppLocalIPv4AddressType
tmnxPppLocalIPv4AddressType.description: tmnxPppLocalIPv4AddressType indicates the address type of the address at the local end of the PPP link.

tmnxPppLocalIPv4Address.name: tmnxPppLocalIPv4Address
tmnxPppLocalIPv4Address.description: tmnxPppLocalIPv4Address indicates the IPv4 address of the local end of the PPP link.

tmnxPppLocalIPv6AddressType.name: tmnxPppLocalIPv6AddressType
tmnxPppLocalIPv6AddressType.description: tmnxPppLocalIPv6AddressType indicates the address type of the address at the local end of the PPP link.

tmnxPppLocalIPv6Address.name: tmnxPppLocalIPv6Address
tmnxPppLocalIPv6Address.description: tmnxPppLocalIPv6Address indicates the IPv6 address of the local end of the PPP link.

tmnxPppRemoteIPv4AddressType.name: tmnxPppRemoteIPv4AddressType
tmnxPppRemoteIPv4AddressType.description: tmnxPppRemoteIPv4AddressType indicates the address type of the address at the remote end of the PPP link.

tmnxPppRemoteIPv4Address.name: tmnxPppRemoteIPv4Address
tmnxPppRemoteIPv4Address.description: tmnxPppRemoteIPv4Address indicates the IPv4 address of the remote end of the PPP link.

tmnxPppRemoteIPv6AddressType.name: tmnxPppRemoteIPv6AddressType
tmnxPppRemoteIPv6AddressType.description: tmnxPppRemoteIPv6AddressType indicates the address type of the address at the remote end of the PPP link.

tmnxPppRemoteIPv6Address.name: tmnxPppRemoteIPv6Address
tmnxPppRemoteIPv6Address.description: tmnxPppRemoteIPv6Address indicates the IPv6 address of the remote end of the PPP link.

tmnxPppHdrCompression.name: tmnxPppHdrCompression
tmnxPppHdrCompression.description: The value of tmnxPppHdrCompression specifies Address Control Field Compression (ACFC) and Protocol Field Compression (PFC) behaviour over this PPP link as detailed below. tmnxPppHdrCompression| Protocol action ---------------------|----------------------------------------------- acfc | ACFC is requested in config requests sent and | accepted in config request received pfc | PFC is requested in config requests sent and | accepted in config request received

tmnxPppCpTable.name: tmnxPppCpTable
tmnxPppCpTable.description: The tmnxPppCpTable has an entry for each PPP Control Protocol run on each port in the system that is configured for PPP.

tmnxPppCpEntry.name: tmnxPppCpEntry
tmnxPppCpEntry.description: Each row entry represents a specific Ppp Control Protocol being run on a specific port from the tmnxPortTable that is configured for PPP. Entries cannot be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations; rows are created and deleted by the agent as the tmnxPortClass and tmnxPortEncapType values are modified. For any specific link, there is one Link Control Protocol (LCP) plus one or more Network Control Protocols (NCP) depending on the type of protocols supported on the link: ipcp, mplscp, bcp or osicp.

tmnxPppCpProtocol.name: tmnxPppCpProtocol
tmnxPppCpProtocol.description: The enumerated value of tmnxPppCpProtocol indicates the type of Control Protocol represented by this row entry. For any specific link, there is one Link Control Protocol (LCP) plus one or more Network Control Protocols (NCP) depending on the type of protocols supported on the link: ipcp, mplscp, bcp or osicp.

tmnxPppCpState.name: tmnxPppCpState
tmnxPppCpState.description: The tmnxPppCpState variable indicates the current state of the PPP Control Protocol on this interface.

tmnxPppCpLastChange.name: tmnxPppCpLastChange
tmnxPppCpLastChange.description: The last time the value of tmnxPppCpState changed.

tmnxPppCpRestartCount.name: tmnxPppCpRestartCount
tmnxPppCpRestartCount.description: The number of times that this Control Protocol has reached the 'open' state.

tmnxPppCpLastClearedTime.name: tmnxPppCpLastClearedTime
tmnxPppCpLastClearedTime.description: The last time tmnxPppCpRestartCount has been reset to zero.

tmnxPppCpUp.name: tmnxPppCpUp
tmnxPppCpUp.description: Generated when the finite state machine of a control protocol (LCP, LQR, etc.) reaches the OPENED state.

tmnxPppCpDown.name: tmnxPppCpDown
tmnxPppCpDown.description: Generated when the finite state machine of a control protocol (LCP, LQR, etc.) leaves the OPENED state.

tmnxPppNcpUp.name: tmnxPppNcpUp
tmnxPppNcpUp.description: Generated when the finite state machine of a network control protocol (IPCP, MPLSCP, BCP, OSICP, etc.) reaches the OPENED state.

tmnxPppNcpDown.name: tmnxPppNcpDown
tmnxPppNcpDown.description: Generated when the finite state machine of a network control protocol (IPCP, MPLSCP, BCP, OSICP, etc.) leaves the OPENED state.

tmnxPppKeepaliveFailure.name: tmnxPppKeepaliveFailure
tmnxPppKeepaliveFailure.description: Generated when the keepalive based on echo packets failed.

tmnxPppLqmFailure.name: tmnxPppLqmFailure
tmnxPppLqmFailure.description: Generated when the link has failed in meeting the specified quality percentage.

tmnxPppLoopback.name: tmnxPppLoopback
tmnxPppLoopback.description: Generated when the value of tmnxPppLocalMagicNumber is the same as the value of tmnxPppRemoteMagicNumber sent by the peer.

tmnxPppLoopbackClear.name: tmnxPppLoopbackClear
tmnxPppLoopbackClear.description: Generated when the loopback condition is cleared. It means that the value of tmnxPppLocalMagicNumber is different than the value of tmnxPppRemoteMagicNumber sent by the peer.

tmnxPppCompliance.name: tmnxPppCompliance
tmnxPppCompliance.description: The compliance statement for management of PPP protocol features using the TIMETRA-PPP-MIB.

tmnxPpp7450V4v0Compliance.name: tmnxPpp7450V4v0Compliance
tmnxPpp7450V4v0Compliance.description: The compliance statement for management of PPP protocol features for revision 4.0 on the Alcatel 7450 SR series systems.

tmnxPpp7750V4v0Compliance.description: The compliance statement for management of PPP protocol features for revision 4.0 on the Alcatel 7750 SR series systems.

tmnxPpp7450V6v0Compliance.description: The compliance statement for management of PPP protocol features for revision 6.0 on the Alcatel 7450 SR series systems.

tmnxPpp77x0V6v0Compliance.name: tmnxPpp77x0V6v0Compliance
tmnxPpp77x0V6v0Compliance.description: The compliance statement for management of PPP protocol features for revision 6.0 on the Alcatel 77x0 SR series systems.

tmnxPppGroup.name: tmnxPppGroup
tmnxPppGroup.description: The group of objects supporting management of Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP) capabilities on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPppNotificationGroup.name: tmnxPppNotificationGroup
tmnxPppNotificationGroup.description: The group of notifications supporting the management of Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP) on Alcatel 7x50 SR series systems.

tmnxPPPObsoleteV4v0Group.name: tmnxPPPObsoleteV4v0Group
tmnxPPPObsoleteV4v0Group.description: The group of objects in TIMETRA-PPP-MIB which are obsoleted.

tmnxPpp7450V4v0Group.name: tmnxPpp7450V4v0Group
tmnxPpp7450V4v0Group.description: The group of objects supporting management of Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP) capabilities on the 4.0 version of Alcatel 7450 SR systems.

tmnxPpp7750V4v0Group.name: tmnxPpp7750V4v0Group
tmnxPpp7750V4v0Group.description: The group of objects supporting management of Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP) capabilities on the 4.0 version of Alcatel 7750 SR systems.

tmnxPppCompressionGroup.name: tmnxPppCompressionGroup
tmnxPppCompressionGroup.description: The group of objects supporting management of compression capabilities over Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP) interfaces on the Alcatel 7750 SR systems.
